|CKBFormat:|WK0
    (Living_Object)->set_attribute("extra_hp_function", 
        ({ Source_Object/Source_Object_File, .. }) );

|CKBDescription:|WK0
    Will add the result from call_other(
        Source_Object/Source_Object_File, "extra_hp_function")
        to the monitor ("hp", ".", "st") for each object/file
        in the array.

|CKBExample:|WK0
    (this_player())->set_attribute("extra_hp_function",
        ({ "/guilds/ex/ex_bar_maker.c" }) );
    Will call the extra_hp_function() on the ex_bar_maker.c file
        and add it to the monitor, while removing whatever
        object(s)/file(s) were called previously.

To add another file to the array and keep whatever files/objects
    are being called already:

    this_player()->set_attribute("extra_hp_function",( 
        this_player()->query_attribute("extra_hp_function") ? 
        (this_player()->query_attribute("extra_hp_function") + 
        ({ NEW_OBJECT/NEW_FILE })) : ({ NEW_OBJECT/NEW_FILE }));
